projects.title: International Fashion Weeks (IFW)
projects.description:
During INTERNATIONAL Fashion Weeks (IFW) I styled the fashion show of well know Dutch bagdesigner Omar Munie on Saturday the 9th of March 2019. I also helped with the styling of the openingsshow for Houda El Fechka-Eddiouane.

On top of that I organized and styled my own Trend Show during INTERNATIONAL Fashion Weeks (IFW). Here I styled sixteen models (male and female) with outfits inspired by the autumn/winter trends for 2019/2020.

profile_positions.description:
Working within a financial environment where customers are the center of attention. 

Offering ways to solve problems occurring while applying for a new bankaccount via the website, answering questions regarding everything involved with a personal or corporate bankaccount and supplying information.

Within the department I also got the opportunity to coach new colleagues and help them develop their skills.
profile_positions.title: Financial Advisor

profile_positions.description:
This was a dynamic role consisting of various tasks. Communication was key while being the first face that (potential) members saw when entering the gym. Always ready to help members with their questions, apply information about memberships, solve problems that occurred while members were using the facilities and engage in social small talk to put members at ease. 

During the daily shifts it was also necessary to keep track of the stock. This to ensure that all the food and beverages were available at the counter for commercial purposes. Of course the job entailed answering incoming phone calls with sufficient information about the club. As usual cleaning also played a big role (e.g. washing mugs, cleansing the counter and lounge, refilling the coffee machine etc.).

As from the first of September 2020 the premium club was taken over by Basic Fit. Tasks were fairly the same other than the fact of implementing new membership forms. The installment of several new machines was ensured to improve automation of existing processes (e.g. machines for people to subscribe and get their membership card and clubcard scanners in order to open the door), however this also created the task of helping people using the machines.
profile_positions.title: Reception Administrative Assistant

profile_positions.description:
This function consisted of many different aspects within the field of communication and fashion styling.  In order to do so it was necessary to maintain contact with photographers, graphic designers and influential people within the fashion industry.

Writing copy for flyers and brochures was one of the main components. These written products are still used today. The flyers are handed out to in-store customers and clients, but are also used during events as a way of advertising. 

The importance of social media in today's society lead to the development of an improvement proposal for the brand's social pages on Facebook and Instagram. This plan was partially implemented by starting a different posting strategy while using the functionalities within the apps. It also included the development of an online Easter contest within Instagram to enhance engagement and following. Taking pictures and writing copy for LinkedIn were also included. 

During INTERNATIONAL Fashion Weeks the brand had their own fashion show where I was in charge of styling twenty-six models. After researching the upcoming trends for spring/summer 2019 I came up with a concept and made sure it was executed correctly.
profile_positions.title: Freelance Communication Specialist & Fashion Stylist

profile_positions.description: The main focus concerned helping the customers by giving personal advice. Therefore it was essential to stay up-to-date with the collection (either in store as online). Just as in every store it was important to keep up with the stock supply. This means booking in the deliveries and making sure every clothing item was labeled and provided with a price tag. I also got the chance to style the mannequins in accordance to the seasonal trends.
profile_positions.title: Assistant Sales

profile_positions.description:
Tasks were dependent of the assignement given. The red thread mainly consisted of the following steps: reading about the subject and doing research about it, contacting the spokesperson in order to plan an interview, drawing up interview questions, the interview itself (while recording it), writing down valuable information collected during the interview, process everything into a story for the article.

De Posthoorn values authentic images for the newspaper. This is why it was always necessary to take pictures. If the pictures were approved they were incorporated into the article.
profile_positions.title: Freelance journalist

profile_positions.description:
Tasks alternated swiftly. Writing e-mails, but also answering and placing phone calls were an essential part of the daily routine. This all contributed to maintaining the relationship with (potential) clients. It was also frequently necessary to send out requests in order to borrow clothes and accessories for famous Dutch actors and/or artists.  

On top of this I selected clothes, accessories and shoes for editorial photoshoots and televisionshows (eg. 'Dance Dance Dance', 'Heel Holland Bakt' and 'De Brabander Bakt'). Selections were made in PR agencies, shops and online stores with a moodboard as guideline. The collected items were combined into sets, in order to do a fitting with the customer. Returning items and drawing up invoices were also included in the job.

In addition I got the chance to accompany several productions from beginning till end. In order to do so the first step was to make a moodboard. Afterwards photographers, make-up artists and modelling agencies were contacted in order to form a team. I booked a venue that matched the theme and after fulfilling all these tasks it was time to collect the clothes in order to make different sets. During the day of the shoot I lead the team to the best results possible.
profile_positions.title: Personal Assistant

profile_positions.description:
Witin the company of NIBC internal users were helped when they experienced difficulties with their laptop, surface, desktop and/or mobile phone (iOs and Andriod). Communication took place via telephone, face-to-face, via e-mail and via Skype. Incidents and requests were registered in Topdesk. Tasks consisted of registering and prioritizing incidents and requests, solving incidents and requests, escalating incidents and requests and sending applications to users via SCCM. On top of this there was also time to participate in several projects. New equipment was registered within the CMDB in order to deliver these items to the users. Besides this the department also invested time and energy into the optimization of accessiblity and visibility of equipment. 

Within Qiss-it (secondment agency) there was contributed to the development of a new marketing strategy and promotional material for the 'Carrierebeurs'. Video footage was recorded and edited into short clips in order to reach the target audience. These clips were posted on several social media accounts.
profile_positions.title: Customer Service Specialist

profile_positions.description:
Clients could contact the service desk when they had questions regarding their membership. Within the departement the main focus included the extra channel packages and processing terminations of mobile telephone memberships. Alternations were incerted into the database called EBS and/or Telena. All the calls were logged with Quicklog. 

Clients with other questions were transferred to the appropriate departement.
profile_positions.title: Customer Sales and Service Representative

profile_positions.description: As an administrative assistant main tasks consisted of editing invoices, schedule meetings and appointments, reading and replying to e-mails, but also answering questions of clients over the phone.
profile_positions.title: Assistant Administrative

volunteer_experiences.description: Enlighten students about their post high school choices. Giving them advice about the difference between following a study at the HBO (Hoger Beroeps Onderwijs) or at the university. I also talked  about my personal career choices in order to give them some insights about the fashion industry and my work as a fashion stylist.
